    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/s3x280-0x/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=615264230282625862&sectionId=615264230332957510)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"off_lazy_script"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggzQNDTTgV1_text","label":"ggzQNDTTgV1_text","default":"<strong>I Spent 90 Days Investigating </strong><span style=\"background-color:rgba(249, 195, 47, 0.77);\"><strong>MeridEase Labs' Pumpkin Seed Oil and Saw Palmetto Softgels</strong></span><strong> to See If They Actually Work. Here's What I Found.</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg0xBVISNIu_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg0xBVISNIu_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/hf_20260306_110622_b91e79d5-46ea-473f-b7fa-9c0614e78dec.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gggnu-lAaJZ_text","label":"gggnu-lAaJZ_text","default":"<p><span style=\"color:#000000;font-size:18px;\">By Dr. Mike Reynolds, MD, Urologist | 22 Years in Practice</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggKKnEsidaS_text","label":"ggKKnEsidaS_text","default":"<p><i>Clever marketing or a real answer for men who can't sleep through the night? I looked at the actual science.</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggm20EezU0k_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggm20EezU0k_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_jh7z5ujh7z5ujh7z_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggm20EezU0k_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggm20EezU0k_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_jh7z5ujh7z5ujh7z_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggeI6Clv8WX_text","label":"ggeI6Clv8WX_text","default":"If you've tried Flomax, finasteride, or prostate supplements without sleeping through the night...<br><br>...chances are your prostate is still inflamed.<br><br>That's the real problem most doctors miss.<br><br>What if you could stop waking up 4, 5, 6 times a night...<br><br>...not by relaxing muscles for a few hours...<br><br>...but by cooling the inflammation that's keeping your prostate swollen in the first place?<br><br>That's exactly what MeridEase Labs' Pumpkin Seed Oil and Saw Palmetto Softgels are built to do.<br><br>A natural way to target the root cause and get your sleep back."},{"type":"html","id":"ggFHX5C0Gbe_text","label":"ggFHX5C0Gbe_text","default":"<strong>The Question Every Man Is Asking</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg4_hAqfcUI_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg4_hAqfcUI_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/istockphoto-121546719-612x612.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"gg4_hAqfcUI_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"gg4_hAqfcUI_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/istockphoto-121546719-612x612.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggh160fHHML_text","label":"ggh160fHHML_text","default":"<p>My inbox has been flooded with the same question.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>\"Do pumpkin seed oil and saw palmetto actually work for BPH, or is this just another supplement that does nothing?\"</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I've been a practicing urologist for 22 years.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I've prescribed every drug available for prostate problems.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Flomax. Finasteride. Avodart. Cialis for BPH. All of it.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>When this pack started getting attention in patient forums, I was skeptical.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The claims seemed impossible:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>- Reduces nighttime bathroom trips without a prescription</p><p>- Targets the actual root cause of prostate swelling</p><p>- No dependency, no withdrawal</p><p>- Men sleeping through the night within weeks</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>But hundreds of men, including some of my own patients, were asking about it.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>So I investigated.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggslWqaQtq2_text","label":"ggslWqaQtq2_text","default":"<strong>The 90-Day Investigation</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg720e49VOk_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg720e49VOk_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_x4i5pmx4i5pmx4i5_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"gg720e49VOk_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"gg720e49VOk_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Homework-A-Help-or-a-Hindrance-900x675.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggG-7I2VKMm_text","label":"ggG-7I2VKMm_text","default":"<p>I wasn't going to trust supplement marketing. <strong>I needed real data.</strong><br><br>Here's what I did:</p><ul><li>Reviewed 9 peer-reviewed studies on pumpkin seed oil and prostate inflammation.</li><li>Interviewed 47 men who had been using the softgels for at least 30 days.</li><li>Monitored 14 of my own patients who added the softgels to their routine.</li><li>Tried the softgels myself.</li></ul>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggXJohDDRgt_text","label":"ggXJohDDRgt_text","default":"<strong>What I Found: The Science</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6Cfe6f29k_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg6Cfe6f29k_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/enlarged-prostate.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"gg6Cfe6f29k_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"gg6Cfe6f29k_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_6qy0cd6qy0cd6qy0_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUfcz6uXll_text","label":"ggUfcz6uXll_text","default":"<p>Here's what shocked me.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>For most of my career, I was trained that <strong>BPH is a hormone problem.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Too much DHT. The prostate grows. Block the hormone or relax the muscles. That's the standard plan.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>But that's only half the story.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The research shows BPH starts with inflammation.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Chronic, low-grade inflammation inside the prostate tissue.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Inflammatory signals called IL-6 and TNF-alpha flood the area.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Immune cells rush in.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The tissue swells and turns rigid.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>And rigid tissue does not relax between bathroom trips.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>That's why you feel the urge even right after you went.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p>That's why you never fully empty.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Then DHT shows up and <strong>binds far more easily to inflamed tissue than healthy tissue.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>So now you have two things feeding each other.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Inflammation making the tissue rigid. DHT making the prostate grow faster.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>That's why men who try a generic saw palmetto capsule feel nothing.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Saw palmetto alone only touches DHT.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The inflammation keeps burning.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>But there's a critical difference.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Flomax relaxes the muscles around your urethra for a few hours. You take it, it helps, then it wears off. Your prostate never shrinks. The inflammation never stops. You're fully dependent on it just to get through the night.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>MeridEase Labs' cold-pressed pumpkin seed oil does something different.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>It delivers a full complex of phytosterols directly to the inflamed prostate tissue.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>They block the cytokine signals. They calm the immune cell rush. The tissue starts to soften.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>When the tissue softens, the urethra stops being squeezed so tight.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Flow improves. The urge settles. Nighttime trips drop.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>MeridEase Labs isn't masking the problem.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>It's putting out the fire.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGMAIS7s5m_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggGMAIS7s5m_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_4ty0o4ty0o4ty0o4_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggGMAIS7s5m_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggGMAIS7s5m_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_4ty0o4ty0o4ty0o4_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggIIxvV39Tx_text","label":"ggIIxvV39Tx_text","default":"<p>And the saw palmetto extract adds one more layer.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Its fatty acids <strong>block DHT from binding to prostate cell receptors.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>So DHT is double-blocked.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Production goes down. Receptor binding goes down.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>And saw palmetto independently calms the bladder neck, reducing the muscle spasm that triggers urgency <strong>before your bladder is even close to full.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>That's why this works when generic saw palmetto capsules don't.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Two ingredients. Three fires out.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Not masked. Not pushed down temporarily. Extinguished.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggMnidJ-jPR_text","label":"ggMnidJ-jPR_text","default":"<strong>Why Your Doctor Has Never Mentioned This</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfqlLnQDly_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggfqlLnQDly_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_ysadt1ysadt1ysad_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggfqlLnQDly_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggfqlLnQDly_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_ysadt1ysadt1ysad_1.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggaG0C73vSq_text","label":"ggaG0C73vSq_text","default":"<p>Here's the uncomfortable truth I have to share as a physician.<br><br><strong>MeridEase Labs' softgels are not a prescription drug.</strong><br><br>That means:</p><ul><li>No pharmaceutical company profits from them.</li><li>No drug reps educating doctors about them.</li><li>No insurance billing code for recommending them.</li><li>No incentive for a doctor to bring it up.</li></ul><p><br>I asked 13 urologists in my network about it.<br><br>Only one had ever heard of using pumpkin seed oil for BPH.<br><br>None had recommended it to a patient.<br><br><strong>Not because it doesn't work. Because they didn't know it existed.</strong><br><br>The medical system is built around prescriptions. Everything else is invisible.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwChdnTNBJ_text","label":"ggwChdnTNBJ_text","default":"<strong>The Problems With Flomax Nobody Discusses</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggaBF89G2wF_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggaBF89G2wF_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/766x415_Flomax_Side_Effects.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggaBF89G2wF_srcSet_mobile_src","label":"ggaBF89G2wF_srcSet_mobile_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/766x415_Flomax_Side_Effects.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggC1d7H_Cy0_text","label":"ggC1d7H_Cy0_text","default":"<p>Most men on Flomax don't have the full picture.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>You'll need it forever.</strong> Your prostate never shrinks. The inflammation never cools.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Many men deal with dizziness every time they stand up.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Others experience<strong> retrograde ejaculation.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Low blood pressure that gets dangerous during physical activity.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>And for many men, <strong>it keeps working less and less over time as tolerance builds.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>One of my patients told me:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>\"My doctor kept increasing my dose. Then even the highest dose stopped helping. He said surgery might be next. That's when I started looking for something else.\"</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Meanwhile, the inflammation is still burning.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The prostate is still growing.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The drug is just papering over it.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNaDtqUOVv_text","label":"ggNaDtqUOVv_text","default":"<strong>My Professional Assessment</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPWMLeDUZm_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggPWMLeDUZm_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0809/8739/0192/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_gwo43kgwo43kgwo4.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggdAN9Q1Dgi_text","label":"ggdAN9Q1Dgi_text","default":"<p>After 90 days of reviewing the science and watching my own patients...</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Yes. MeridEase Labs' Pumpkin Seed Oil and Saw Palmetto Softgels work. And for most men over 50, they go after something Flomax never touches.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Not faster than Flomax at first. Flomax wins on speed.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>But <strong>cooling actual inflammation versus relaxing muscles temporarily?</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>MeridEase wins decisively.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>No dependency.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>No retrograde ejaculation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>No blood pressure crashes.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>No building tolerance month after month.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Actual reduction in prostate swelling over time.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>That is the difference between masking a problem and solving it.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggblP80kboX_text","label":"ggblP80kboX_text","default":"<strong>Who Should Try This?</strong>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggh9cc1rGQp_text","label":"ggh9cc1rGQp_text","default":"<ul><li>Men waking up 3 or more times a night</li><li>Men who feel Flomax is working less and less</li><li>Men who can't stand the side effects of their current medication</li><li>Men who have been told surgery might be the next step</li><li>Men who tried generic saw palmetto and felt nothing</li><li>Men who want to fix the root cause, not rent relief month to month</li></ul>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8U7KKNzEG_text"